eNCA’s Siphamandla Goge reports. Courtesy #DStv403 LERATSWANA, Free State - Suspended ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule, says step-aside or no step-aside resolution - he’ll contest the party’s national elections in December. The ANC National Executive Committee resolved that criminally charged members and leaders can’t stand for leadership positions until they are cleared. READ: Magashule: 'I must be allowed to prove my innocence' Magashule, who is facing corruption charges, was suspended for refusing to step aside. He is due back in court on Friday - for pre-trial proceedings and the possible setting of a trial date for his corruption case.